<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,885,1269]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1029,1053]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks:</emphasis>
According to Rosalie de Lamarck, her father’s collection contained 
<specimenCount box="[1099,1283,1029,1053]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
. However, as none of the specimens currently in the Lamarck collection matches Lamarck or Kiener’s figures, nor Lamarck’s stated sizes, it is unlikely that these are Lamarck’s original specimens. Confusingly, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamarck" box="[1118,1301,1101,1125]" firstAuthor="Lamarck" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref11267" refString="Lamarck, [J. B. P. A.] (1822) Histoire naturelle des animaux sans vertebres ... Paris. 7 (2), 711 pp." type="book" year="1822">Lamarck (1822)</bibRefCitation>
lists 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Muricidae" genus="Murex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lignarius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Murex lignarius</emphasis>
Linnaeus
</taxonomicName>
in the synonymy of this species. This is a different species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,885,1269]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,558,1173,1198]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Current taxonomic position:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[575,975,1173,1197]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Euthria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cornea">
<emphasis box="[575,755,1173,1197]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Euthria cornea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus" box="[779,967,1173,1197]" firstAuthor="Linnaeus" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref11299" refString="Linnaeus, C. von. (1758) Systema naturae per regna tria naturae. Editio decima, reformata. Vol. 1. Regnum animale. Stockholm. 824, iii pp." type="book" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<typeStatus box="[997,1045,1174,1198]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gray, 1850" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1850" box="[1200,1436,1173,1197]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Euthria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1200,1286,1173,1197]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Euthria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gray" box="[1302,1436,1173,1197]" firstAuthor="Gray" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref10511" refString="Gray, J. E. (1850) [New generic assignments] In: M. E. Gray. Figures of molluscous animals, selected from various authors. Etched for the use of students. Volume 4. Explanations of plates and list of genera. London: Longman, Brown, Green and Longmans. iv, 219 pp." type="book" year="1850">Gray, 1850</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
[
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[157,291,1209,1233]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Buccinidae</taxonomicName>
], placed in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[622,1004,1209,1233]" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" genus="Euthria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cornea">
